[2] Cote d'Ivoire
Date: Thu 22 Mar 2012
Source: AllAfrica.com [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201203230695.html

An outbreak of meningitis has claimed the lives of a dozen people in the western town of Toulepleu according to a report by Le Nouveau Reveil. The epidemic, the paper said, is spreading quickly throughout the war-torn city despite the timely reaction of the Ivorian government which has delivered drugs to the area and is undertaking measures to curb the disease.

