me

[There are at least 13 serogroups of _Neisseria meningitidis_ based on the antigenic specificity of their capsular polysaccharides; disease is most commonly due to serogroups A, B, C, Y, and W135. All these serogroup polysaccharides except B are immunogenic in humans. Rarely outbreaks of meningococcal meningitis have been related to other serogroups such as type X which has occurred in Niger in 2006 and Burkina Faso in 2010. - Mod. LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1IeR.]
